examples.en: The house had a neglected air.
The building has been neglected for years.
Children who are neglected tend to become neglectful parents.
Shaw's neglected one-act comedy, 'A Village Wooing'.
The prison guard neglected his duty.
He discussed the general but neglected the particular.
He neglected his health and paid the penalty.
The city has neglected the teacher shortage for too long.
Many of these ideas have been neglected by modern historians.
The company neglected to publicize the side effects of the new drug.
Politicians have neglected our military posture.
He felt a deep remorse for having neglected his family over the years.
The deceitful salesman neglected to mention some important information about the used car.
